A police officer was yesterday killed during an attack by hoodlums on a police patrol team at Akwukwu-Igbo, the administrative headquarters of Oshimili North local government area of Delta State. It was gathered that the incident occurred at about 8am on Wednesday. The police van the team was using was reportedly set ablaze by the hoodlums. Some of the officers sustained varying degree of injuries. The policemen were said to be on a stop-and-search duty when the hoodlums attacked them along Otulu-Akwukwu Igbo road. The police officer reportedly died on the spot. The police public relations officer, DSP Bright Edafe, confirmed the incident when contacted.